<item>
            <title>[FLINK-36172] Web UI Freezes When There Are Many Finished Tasks in Batch Jobs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-36172</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When there are a large number of finished tasks in batch jobs, the web UI becomes unresponsive and often freezes, significantly impairing user experience. A flame graph analysis reveals that most CPU time is consumed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/576ec2b9361a3f8d58fb22b998b0ca7c3c8cf10e/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/rest/handler/legacy/metrics/MetricStore.java#L479&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;MetricStore&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, indicating a performance bottleneck.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue appears to be an unexpected regression and should be addressed promptly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
